               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I married my first wife by the parish, and lived unhappy. On proof of her infidelity, we parted by mutual consent. I got acquainted with my second wife - she was in the family way by me, and urged me to marry, and threatened to swear the child to me; and being alarmed, I married her - not knowing I was doing wrong.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220417-72-person677">
                  BRIDGET 
                  GRAYDON
               <interp inst="t18220417-72-person677" type="surname" value="GRAYDON"></interp>
